00059 /* Current major and minor versions of the CVMX bootinfo block that is passed
00060 ** from the bootloader to the application.  This is versioned so that applications
00061 ** can properly handle multiple bootloader versions. */
00062 #define CVMX_BOOTINFO_MAJ_VER 1
00063 #define CVMX_BOOTINFO_MIN_VER 4
00064 
00065 #if (CVMX_BOOTINFO_MAJ_VER == 1)
00066 #define CVMX_BOOTINFO_OCTEON_SERIAL_LEN 20
00067 /* This structure is populated by the bootloader.  For binary
00068 ** compatibility the only changes that should be made are
00069 ** adding members to the end of the structure, and the minor
00070 ** version should be incremented at that time.
00071 ** If an incompatible change is made, the major version
00072 ** must be incremented, and the minor version should be reset
00073 ** to 0.
00074 */
00075 struct cvmx_bootinfo {
00076 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
00077     uint32_t major_version;
00078     uint32_t minor_version;
00079 
00080     uint64_t stack_top;
00081     uint64_t heap_base;
00082     uint64_t heap_end;
00083     uint64_t desc_vaddr;
00084 
00085     uint32_t exception_base_addr;
00086     uint32_t stack_size;
00087     uint32_t flags;
00088     uint32_t core_mask; /**< Old core mask limited to 32 cores, deprecated */
00089     uint32_t dram_size;
00090              /**< DRAM size in megabytes */
00091     uint32_t phy_mem_desc_addr;
00092                  /**< physical address of free memory descriptor block*/
00093     uint32_t debugger_flags_base_addr;
00094                     /**< used to pass flags from app to debugger */
00095     uint32_t eclock_hz;
00096              /**< CPU clock speed, in hz */
00097     uint32_t dclock_hz;
00098              /**< DRAM clock speed, in hz */
00099     uint32_t reserved0;
00100     uint16_t board_type;
00101     uint8_t board_rev_major;
00102     uint8_t board_rev_minor;
00103     uint16_t reserved1;
00104     uint8_t reserved2;
00105     uint8_t reserved3;
00106     char board_serial_number[CVMX_BOOTINFO_OCTEON_SERIAL_LEN];
00107     uint8_t mac_addr_base[6];
00108     uint8_t mac_addr_count;
00109 #if (CVMX_BOOTINFO_MIN_VER >= 1)
00110     /* Several boards support compact flash on the Octeon boot bus.  The CF
00111      * memory spaces may be mapped to different addresses on different
00112      * boards.  These are the physical addresses, so care must be taken
00113      * to use the correct XKPHYS/KSEG0 addressing depending on the
00114      * application's ABI.  These values will be 0 if CF is not present
00115      *
00116      * Note that this is deprecated since this is now in the device tree.
00117      */
00118     uint64_t compact_flash_common_base_addr;
00119     uint64_t compact_flash_attribute_base_addr;
00120     /* Base address of the LED display (as on EBT3000 board)
00121      * This will be 0 if LED display not present.
00122      *
00123      * This is deprecated since this data is now in the device tree.
00124      */
00125     uint64_t led_display_base_addr;
00126 #endif
00127 #if (CVMX_BOOTINFO_MIN_VER >= 2)
00128     uint32_t dfa_ref_clock_hz;
00129                 /**< DFA reference clock in hz (if applicable)*/
00130     uint32_t config_flags;
00131                 /**< flags indicating various configuration options.  These flags supercede
00132                             ** the 'flags' variable and should be used instead if available */
00133 #endif
00134 #if (CVMX_BOOTINFO_MIN_VER >= 3)
00135     uint64_t fdt_addr;
00136             /**< Address of the OF Flattened Device Tree structure describing the board. */
00137 #endif
00138 #if (CVMX_BOOTINFO_MIN_VER >= 4)
00139             /**<
00140              * Coremask used for processors with more than 32 cores
00141              * or with OCI.  This replaces core_mask.
00142              */
00143     cvmx_coremask_t ext_core_mask;
00144 #endif
00145 #else               /* __BIG_ENDIAN */
00146     /*
00147      * Little-Endian: When the CPU mode is switched to
00148      * little-endian, the view of the structure has some of the
00149      * fields swapped.
00150      */
00151     uint32_t minor_version;
00152     uint32_t major_version;
00153 
00154     uint64_t stack_top;
00155     uint64_t heap_base;
00156     uint64_t heap_end;
00157     uint64_t desc_vaddr;
00158 
00159     uint32_t stack_size;
00160     uint32_t exception_base_addr;
00161 
00162     uint32_t core_mask;
00163     uint32_t flags;
00164 
00165     uint32_t phy_mem_desc_addr;
00166     uint32_t dram_size;
00167 
00168     uint32_t eclock_hz;
00169     uint32_t debugger_flags_base_addr;
00170 
00171     uint32_t reserved0;
00172     uint32_t dclock_hz;
00173 
00174     uint8_t reserved3;
00175     uint8_t reserved2;
00176     uint16_t reserved1;
00177     uint8_t board_rev_minor;
00178     uint8_t board_rev_major;
00179     uint16_t board_type;
00180 
00181     char board_serial_number[CVMX_BOOTINFO_OCTEON_SERIAL_LEN];
00182     uint8_t mac_addr_base[6];
00183     uint8_t mac_addr_count;
00184     uint8_t pad[5];
00185 
00186 #if (CVMX_BOOTINFO_MIN_VER >= 1)
00187     uint64_t compact_flash_common_base_addr;
00188     uint64_t compact_flash_attribute_base_addr;
00189     uint64_t led_display_base_addr;
00190 #endif
00191 #if (CVMX_BOOTINFO_MIN_VER >= 2)
00192     uint32_t config_flags;
00193     uint32_t dfa_ref_clock_hz;
00194 #endif
00195 #if (CVMX_BOOTINFO_MIN_VER >= 3)
00196     uint64_t fdt_addr;
00197 #endif
00198 #if (CVMX_BOOTINFO_MIN_VER >= 4)
00199     cvmx_coremask_t ext_core_mask;
00200 #endif
00201 #endif
00202 };

00206 #define CVMX_BOOTINFO_CFG_FLAG_PCI_HOST         (1ull << 0)
00207 #define CVMX_BOOTINFO_CFG_FLAG_PCI_TARGET       (1ull << 1)
00208 #define CVMX_BOOTINFO_CFG_FLAG_DEBUG            (1ull << 2)
00209 #define CVMX_BOOTINFO_CFG_FLAG_NO_MAGIC         (1ull << 3)
00210 /* This flag is set if the TLB mappings are not contained in the
00211 ** 0x10000000 - 0x20000000 boot bus region. */
00212 #define CVMX_BOOTINFO_CFG_FLAG_OVERSIZE_TLB_MAPPING     (1ull << 4)
00213 #define CVMX_BOOTINFO_CFG_FLAG_BREAK            (1ull << 5)

00215 #endif /*   (CVMX_BOOTINFO_MAJ_VER == 1) */

00219 /* the following structure extend bootinfo with common for all cores data
00220  * It will be put in named block. No need of locking - it will be written just
00221  * once from the bootloader and will be only read from others
00222  */
00223 #define CVMX_COMMON_BOOTINFO_MAGIC  0x1234567887654321
00224 #define CVMX_COMMON_BOOTINFO_VERSION    1   /* 1 based */
00225 #define CVMX_APP_COMMON_BOOTINFO_NAME   "__common_bootinfo"
00226 #define CVMX_APP_COMMON_BOOTINFO_SIZE   sizeof(cvmx_cores_common_bootinfo_t)
00227 
00228 struct cvmx_cores_common_bootinfo {
00229     uint64_t    magic;
00230     uint64_t    version; /*keep simple - we do not plan other versions*/
00231     cvmx_coremask_t hardware_coremask;
00232     cvmx_coremask_t avail_coremask;
00233 #if (CVMX_COMMON_BOOTINFO_VERSION >= 2)
00234     /* declare ver2_members here*/;
00235 #endif
00236 };
